@loropiana isn't just the century-old textile mill behind some of the world's finest tailoring fabrics, nor merely the maker of stealth-wealth essentials and $225 frisbees. It's also quietly become one of luxury's most compelling outdoor brands.⁠
⁠
The proof lies in its proprietary performance technologies. Storm System, Loro Piana's answer to GORE-TEX, brings waterproofing and wind resistance to its premium materials, while graphene-infused Clima System prioritizes breathability and temperature regulation. Together, they power a growing range of elevated outdoor gear, from fully waterproof Merino wool bombers and packable technical outerwear to backpacks, ski gloves, sleeping bags, and even hiking boots developed with ROA. It's not hardcore alpine equipment, but rather a refined take on trail-ready clothing that sits closer to Arc'teryx Veilance than traditional luxury fashion. If "quiet luxury" was Loro Piana's calling card, consider this its mastery of "quiet outdoor."⁠

@dior is expanding its lifestyle offering with Haute Wellness, a new collection designed by Cordelia de Castellane that focuses on movement, mindfulness, and better sleep. The range combines a selection of fitness and wellness essentials, all finished with subtle nods to the House, including the signature cannage motif embroidered in gold thread on a palette of blue and ivory.⁠
⁠
The collection includes workout accessories such as resistance bands, weights, yoga and Pilates mats, and water bottles, alongside sleep-focused pieces like a silk pillowcase and eye mask. Rounding out the lineup is the 5 Minutes Journal, designed to encourage a few moments of daily reflection through prompts and quotes.⁠

Who you got?
@nyknicks and @spurs go head to head tonight in Game 1 of the 2026 NBA Finals. The Knicks haven’t won a title since 1973 and are riding an 11-game winning streak into San Antonio. Wembanyama and the Spurs finished with the best record in the West and are hungry for a dynasty of their own.
